From Randal Lee Nicholas Mandock Subject Re The doctrine of Original Sin In article M Michael Walker writes My feeling on baptism is this parents baptize their baby so that the baby has the sanctifying grace of baptism and thus removal of original sin on its soul in the event of an unexpected You are right In John Jesus says Amen amen I say to you no one can enter the kingdom of God without being born of water and That's really what He said and He meant That verse is the definition of I don't have the law book in front of me but there is a canon law that urges parents to baptize their children within one week of birth for the very reason that you Randal Lee Nicholas Mandock Catechist